[h4][b]Installation[/b][/h4]

The good news is that, you can say goodbye to non-CLI and CLI instructions and install the PPA like a Millennium Falcon!

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:gusbemacbe/ppa
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt install suru-plus-pack

Do not you like the PPA? No problem, you can have an alternative here:

You can choose two options - with or without CLI, we recommend strongly to use SVN which is quicker like a Millennium Falcon.

[h5][b]Installation without CLI[/b][/h5]
[url=https://github.com/gusbemacbe/suru-plus/blob/master/instructions_without_cli1.md]For users of before Ubuntu 18.04 and any old and new Debian-derived distributions.[/url]
[url=https://github.com/gusbemacbe/suru-plus/blob/master/instructions_without_cli2.md]For users of Ubuntu 18.04.[/url]

[h5][b]Installation with CLI[/b][/h5]
[url=https://github.com/gusbemacbe/suru-plus/blob/master/instructions_with_cli1.md]For users of old Ubuntu versions, Ubuntu 16.04 and any Debian-derived distributions.[/url]
[url=https://github.com/gusbemacbe/suru-plus/blob/master/instructions_with_cli2.md]For users of Ubuntu 16.04.4 and above, Ubuntu 18.04, Kali Linux and any new Debian-derived distributions.[/url]

